{{Short description|none}} {{pp-sock|small=yes}} {{More citations needed|date=September 2022}} {{for multi|other timelines of modern history|Timelines of modern history|future timelines|Timelines of the future}} {{Centurybox|21}} This is a timeline of the [[21st century]].
== [[2001]]–[[2009]] == <!--The 21st century began in 2001, not 2000 -->
===[[2001]]=== * [[January 15]]: [[Wikipedia]] is launched. * [[January 20]]: ** President [[Joseph Estrada]] of the [[Philippines]] is [[Second EDSA Revolution|ousted]]. ** [[George W. Bush]] is inaugurated as [[President of the United States]]. * [[January 26]]: An [[2001 Gujarat earthquake|earthquake]] strikes [[Gujarat]], [[India]], on [[Republic Day (India)|Republic Day]], resulting in more than 20,000 deaths. * [[May 27]]: [[Dos Palmas kidnappings]]: Twenty tourists are abducted by the [[Abu Sayyaf]] Group terrorists from a popular island resort in the Philippines. * [[June 1]]: Eleven members of the royal family of [[Nepal]], including the king and queen, [[Nepalese royal massacre|are killed]] by Crown Prince [[Dipendra of Nepal|Dipendra]], who wounds himself and dies three days later. * [[September 11]]: [[September 11 attacks]]: [[Al-Qaeda]] terrorists hijack four planes, [[American Airlines Flight 11|crashing]] [[United Airlines Flight 175|two]] into the twin towers of the [[World Trade Center (1973–2001)|World Trade Center]] in [[New York City]], the [[American Airlines Flight 77|third]] plane into [[the Pentagon]] in [[Washington, DC]], while the [[United Airlines Flight 93|fourth]] plane is downed on the outskirts of [[Stonycreek Township, Somerset County, Pennsylvania|Stonycreek Township, Pennsylvania]]. 2,996 people, including 2,977 victims and 19 hijackers, die in the attacks. * [[October 7]]–[[December 17]]: The [[United States invasion of Afghanistan|United States invades Afghanistan]] and topples the [[Islamic Emirate of Afghanistan|Taliban regime]], resulting in a [[War in Afghanistan (2001–2021)|long-term war]]. * [[October 23]]: [[Steve Jobs]] introduces the first [[iPod]]. * [[November 12]]: Crash of [[American Airlines Flight 587]]. * [[December 3]]: [[Enron]] files for Chapter 11 bankruptcy after [[Enron scandal|a series of scandals]]. * [[December 11]]: [[China and the World Trade Organization|China becomes]] a member of the [[World Trade Organization]]. * [[December 19]]: [[The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring]] is released. * [[December 19]]–[[December 20|20]]: During an [[1998–2002 Argentine great depression|economic crisis in Argentina]], the government effectively [[Corralito|freezes all bank accounts]] for twelve months which [[December 2001 riots in Argentina|leads to riots]] and President [[Fernando de la Rúa|de la Rúa]]'s resignation from office. There are five "presidents" in less than a month. * The [[al-Aqsa Intifada]] continues. * [[Dean Kamen]] unveils [[Segway]]. * The media magnate [[Silvio Berlusconi]] is elected [[Prime Minister of Italy]]. {{see also|2001#Deaths}}
===[[2002]]=== * [[January 1]]: The [[Euro]] enters circulation. * [[February 3]] : [[Tom Brady]] leads the [[New England Patriots]] to win their first [[Super Bowl 36|Super Bowl]]; during a nearly two decade span, they would appear in nine, winning six. * [[February 6]]: [[Golden Jubilee of Elizabeth II|Golden Jubilee]] of [[Elizabeth II]]. * [[February 8]]: The [[Algerian Civil War]] ends. * [[February 27]]–[[March 1]]: [[2002 Gujarat riots|Riots and mass killings]] in the Indian state of [[Gujarat]] leave 1,044 dead. * [[March 14]]: [[SpaceX]] is founded by [[Elon Musk]]. * [[May 20]]: [[East Timor]] gains independence. * [[July 1]]: The [[International Criminal Court]] is established. * [[July 9]]: The [[African Union]] is founded. * [[September 19]]: The [[First Ivorian Civil War]] begins. * [[September 23]]: [[Mozilla Firefox]] is released. * [[October 12]]: The [[2002 Bali bombings]] killed 202 people and injured 209 more. * [[October 23]]–[[October 26|26]]: Chechen rebels [[Moscow theater hostage crisis|seize a theater]] in Moscow. Amid this siege, around 200 people died. * [[November 16]]: The [[2002-2004 SARS outbreak]] began in [[Guangdong]]. * [[December 18]]: [[The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers]] is released. * [[Switzerland]] joins the [[United Nations]] as the 190th member. * [[Steve Fossett]] becomes the first person to fly solo nonstop around the world. * Israel starts [[Operation Defensive Shield]] in the West Bank in response to a wave of [[List of Palestinian suicide attacks#2000s|Palestinian suicide attacks]]. * Construction of the [[Israeli West Bank barrier]] begins. * America demands [[Iraq disarmament crisis|Iraq allow unfettered access to weapons inspectors]]. * The [[Guantanamo Bay detention camp]] is established. *[[February 8]]: The [[Algerian Civil War]] ends. * [[Hu Jintao]] is elected as [[General Secretary of the Chinese Communist Party]]. * [[Brazil]] wins the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]]. *[[October 2]]-[[October 23]]: [[D.C. sniper attacks|Beltway sniper attacks]]. {{see also|2002#Deaths}}
===[[2003]]=== * [[February 1]]: [[Space Shuttle Columbia]] [[Space Shuttle Columbia Disaster|disintegrates upon reentry]], killing all 7 astronauts on board. * [[February 20]]: [[The Station nightclub fire]]. * [[March 19]]: The United States [[2003 invasion of Iraq|invades Iraq]] and ousts [[Saddam Hussein]], triggering [[Protests against the Iraq War|worldwide protests]] and an [[Iraq War|8 year war]]. * [[August 5]]: [[2003 Marriott Hotel bombing]] kills 12 people. * [[August 27]]–[[August 29|29]]: The first [[six-party talks]], involving [[South Korea|South]] and [[North Korea]], the [[United States]], [[China]], [[Japan]] and [[Russia]]. * [[November 3]]–[[November 23|23]]: The [[Rose Revolution]] occurs in [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]. * [[December 17]]: [[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King]] is released. * The [[War in Darfur]] begins. * The [[Human Genome Project]] is completed. * The [[Second Congo War]] ends with more than 5 million dead. * The [[Second Liberian Civil War]] ends. * The last [[Volkswagen Beetle]] is made in Mexico, after 65 years in production. * Final flight of the SST (Supersonic Transport) [[Concorde]]. * [[2003 Marriott Hotel bombing]]. {{see also|2003#Deaths}}
===[[2004]]=== * [[February 4]]: [[Facebook]] is formed by [[Mark Zuckerberg]], [[Andrew McCollum]], [[Eduardo Saverin]], [[Dustin Moskovitz]], and [[Chris Hughes]]. * [[February 27]]: The [[2004 SuperFerry 14 bombing]] kills 116 people. * [[March 11]]: [[Madrid train bombings]] killed 193 people and injured around 2,000, Europe's deadliest attack since [[Pan Am Flight 103]]. * [[September 1]]–[[September 3|3]]: On [[September 1st]] (first school day in [[Russia]]), a group of [[Chechens|chechen]] [[terrorists]] [[Beslan school hostage crisis|held students, parents and teachers hostage in Beslan school]], in [[North Ossetia–Alania]]. During three days under attack, 334 people died. * [[October 23]]–[[October 27|27]]: [[Boston Red Sox]] wins the [[2004 World Series|World Series]] for the first time since [[1918 World Series|1918]], ending the [[Curse of the Bambino]]. * [[November 11]]: President of the Palestinian National Authority [[Yasser Arafat]] dies. * [[November 7]]–[[December 23]]: The [[Second Battle of Fallujah]] occurs. It is the deadliest American battle since [[Vietnam War|Vietnam]], killing 95 troops. * [[December 8]]: [[Union of South American Nations]] formed. * [[December 12]]: [[Sony Interactive Entertainment|Sony Computer Entertainment]] launches the [[PlayStation Portable]]. * [[December 26]]: [[2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami|Boxing Day Tsunami]] occurs in [[Indian Ocean]], leading to the deaths of 230,000. * [[Enlargement of NATO|NATO]] and [[2004 enlargement of the European Union|the European Union]] incorporates [[2004 enlargement of the European Union|most of the former Eastern Bloc]]. * [[Spirit (rover)|Spirit]] and [[Opportunity (rover)|Opportunity]] land on [[Mars]]. * [[Orange Revolution]] in [[Ukraine]]. * First surface images of [[Saturn]]'s moon [[Titan (moon)|Titan]]. * [[Death and state funeral of Ronald Reagan]]. {{see also|2004#Deaths}}
===[[2005]]=== * [[January 9]]: [[Second Sudanese Civil War]] ends. * [[February 14]]: ** [[2005 Valentine's Day bombings]]. ** [[YouTube]] is founded by [[Jawed Karim]], [[Chad Hurley]] and [[Steve Chen]]. * [[February 14]]–[[April 27]]: [[Cedar Revolution]] in [[Lebanon]] triggered by the [[assassination of Rafic Hariri]]. * [[February 16]]: The [[Kyoto Protocol]] comes into effect. * [[March 22]]–[[April 11]]: [[Tulip Revolution]] in [[Kyrgyzstan]]. * [[April 2]]–[[April 19|19]]: [[Pope John Paul II]] dies, [[Pope Benedict XVI|Benedict XVI]] becomes Pope. * [[April 9]]: [[Wedding of Prince Charles and Camilla Parker Bowles]]. * [[June 13]]: [[Trial of Michael Jackson#Verdict|Michael Jackson was acquitted on all charges related to the alleged sexual abuse of a 13-year-old boy]]. * [[June 23]]: [[Reddit]] is founded by [[Steve Huffman]], [[Aaron Swartz]] and [[Alexis Ohanian]]. * [[July 7]]: [[7/7 attacks]] on [[London Underground]]. * [[July 26]]–[[July 27|27]]: [[Maharashtra floods of 2005|Floods in Maharashtra, India]] over 1000 peoples died. * [[July 28]]: The [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]] ends its [[The Troubles|military campaign]] in Northern Ireland. * [[July 29]]: [[Michael E. Brown]] confirms [[Eris (dwarf planet)|Eris]]. * [[August 3]]: [[Mahmoud Ahmadinejad]] becomes [[President of Iran]]. * [[August 18]]: [[Peace Mission 2005]], the first joint China–Russia [[military exercise]], begins its eight-day training on the [[Shandong Peninsula]]. * [[August 29]]–[[August 31|31]]: [[Hurricane Katrina]] kills 1,836 people in the [[Gulf of Mexico]]. * [[September 30]]: [[Jyllands-Posten Muhammad cartoons controversy|Controversial drawings of Muhammad]] are printed in the Danish newspaper ''[[Jyllands-Posten]]'', sparking outrage and violent riots by Muslims around the world. * [[October 8]]: 80,000 were killed in [[2005 Kashmir earthquake|an earthquake]] in [[Kashmir]], [[Pakistan]] and [[Afghanistan]]. * [[November 22]]: [[Angela Merkel]] becomes Germany's first female [[Chancellor of Germany|Chancellor]]. * [[November 30]]: Surgeons in France carry out the first human [[face transplant]] with [[Isabelle Dinoire]] becoming the first person to undergo it. * [[Israeli disengagement from Gaza|Israel withdraws from Gaza]]. * [[Second Sudanese Civil War]] ends. {{see also|2005#Deaths}}
===[[2006]]=== * [[January 16]]: [[Ellen Johnson Sirleaf]] becomes President of [[Liberia]], and thus Africa's first elected female head of state. * [[January 25]]: [[Hamas]] wins the [[2006 Palestinian legislative election]]. * [[February 17]]: [[2006 Southern Leyte mudslide]]. * [[February 22]]: [[2006 al-Askari mosque bombing]] turns the escalation of [[sectarian violence in Iraq]] into a full-scale war (the [[Iraqi Civil War (2006-2008)|Iraqi Civil War of 2006-2008]]). * [[March 21]]: [[Twitter]] is launched. * [[April 23]]: [[Spotify]] is launched. * [[May 21]]–[[June 3]]: [[2006 Montenegrin independence referendum|Independence of Montenegro]]. * [[July 11]]: [[2006 Mumbai train bombings|Mumbai bombings]]. * [[August 11]]: [[Guimaras oil spill]]. * [[September 1]]: [[Roblox]] was released by [[David Baszucki]]. * [[September 19]]: A [[2006 Thai coup d'état|coup d'état]] in Thailand overthrows the government of [[Prime Minister of Thailand|Prime Minister]] [[Thaksin Shinawatra]]. * [[October 9]]–[[November 13]]: [[Google]] acquires [[YouTube]] for US$1.65 billion. * [[October 18]]: [[Murder of Shaariibuugiin Altantuyaa|Murder of Altantuya Shaaribuu]]: The [[Mongolia]]n model was murdered in [[Malaysia]]. * [[November 1]]: Former Russian security agent [[Poisoning of Alexander Litvinenko|Alexander Litvinenko dies from poisoning]] in the UK. * [[November 21]]: [[Comprehensive Peace Accord]] ends the [[Nepalese Civil War]]. * [[December 30]]: [[Execution of Saddam Hussein]] by hanging. * [[2006 Lebanon War]]. * [[Mexican Drug War]] begins. * [[Somalia War (2006–2009)|Somalia War of 2006]] begins. * The [[International Astronomical Union]] creates [[IAU definition of planet|the first formal definition of a planet]], and excludes [[Pluto]] from the list. * [[Nintendo]] launches the [[Wii]]. * The [[Baiji]], the Yangtze [[river dolphin]], becomes [[functionally extinct]]. * [[Italy national football team|Italy]] wins [[2006 FIFA World Cup]]. * Israeli soldier [[Gilad Shalit]] was abducted by [[Hamas]]. {{see also|2006#Deaths}}
===[[2007]]=== * [[January 9]]: Introduction of the [[iPhone]]. * [[January 25]]: A [[Fatah–Hamas conflict|civil war]] escalated in the [[Gaza Strip]] throughout June, which resulted in [[Hamas]] eventually driving most [[Fatah]]-loyal forces from the Strip. In reaction, Palestinian president [[Mahmoud Abbas]] dismissed Hamas prime minister [[Ismail Haniyeh]] and dissolved the Hamas-ruled parliament. * [[March 4]]: [[First Ivorian Civil War]] ends. * [[April 16]]: [[Virginia Tech shooting]]. * [[May 3]]: [[Disappearance of Madeleine McCann]]. * [[June 22]]–[[June 24|24]]: [[Chris Benoit double-murder and suicide]]. * [[June 27]]: [[Gordon Brown]] becomes [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]]. * [[August 15]]: [[Saffron Revolution|Anti-government protests]] in [[Myanmar]] suppressed by ruling [[Military junta|junta]]. * [[November 29]]: [[Manila Peninsula siege]]. * [[December 27]]: [[Assassination of Benazir Bhutto]]. * [[2007–2008 world food price crisis|Spike in food prices]] and [[subprime crisis]] help trigger [[Great Recession|global recession]]. * [[First Ivorian Civil War]] ends. {{see also|2007#Deaths}}
===[[2008]]=== [[File:Roadster 2.5 windmills trimmed.jpg|[[Tesla Roadster (first generation)|Tesla Roadster]] launched in 2008, the first mass production lithium-ion battery electric car.|thumb]] * [[May 2]]: ** [[Cyclone Nargis]] kills 133,000 in [[Myanmar]]. ** [[Iron Man (2008 film)|Iron Man]] is released in cinemas, which jump-starts the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]; the MCU becomes the [[List of highest-grossing films|highest-grossing film franchise of all time]]. * [[May 7]]: [[Dmitry Medvedev]] becomes [[President of Russia]]. * [[May 28]]: The [[1st Nepalese Constituent Assembly]] declares [[Nepal]] a republic, ending its [[Kingdom of Nepal|monarchy]]. * [[June 20]]–[[June 21]]: [[MV Princess of the Stars|Sinking of MV Princess of the Stars]]. * [[November 4]]: [[Barack Obama]] is elected to become the first black President of the United States. * [[November 26]]–[[November 29|29]]: [[2008 Mumbai attacks]]. * [[Google Chrome]] is released. * The [[Gaza War (2008–09)|Gaza War]] begins. * [[2008 South Ossetia war]]. * [[Kosovo]] [[2008 Kosovo declaration of independence|declares independence]], though it is not recognised by the United Nations. * Iraqi forces [[Battle of Basra (2008)|crack down]] on [[Muqtada al Sadr]]'s Mahdi forces in Basra and Sadr City. * The [[Large Hadron Collider]] is completed as the world's largest and most powerful [[particle collider]]. * [[Tesla Roadster (first generation)|Tesla Roadster]] launched, the first mass production lithium-ion battery electric car. * Stock markets [[Financial crisis of 2007–2008|plunge]] around the world, signaling the start of the [[Great Recession]]. {{see also|2008#Deaths}}
===[[2009]]=== * [[January 3]]: The cryptocurrency [[Bitcoin]] is launched. * [[January 20]]: [[Barack Obama]] is inaugurated as President of the United States, the first African-American to hold the office. * [[June 16]]: Formation of [[BRICS]] economic bloc. * [[June 19]]: [[Zynga]] release ''[[FarmVille]]''. * [[June 25]]: [[Death of Michael Jackson]]. * [[September 26]]: [[Typhoon Ketsana]] kills 789 people in the Philippines. * [[November 23]]: [[Maguindanao massacre|58 people are abducted and killed]] in the Philippine province of [[Maguindanao]]. * [[December 1]]: [[Treaty of Lisbon]]. * [[December 18]]: [[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]] is released in cinemas and becomes the [[List of highest-grossing films|highest-grossing film of all time]]. * The [[Gaza War (2008–09)|Gaza War]] ends while [[Gaza blockade]] continues. * The [[Sri Lankan Civil War]] ends. * [[2009–2010 Iranian election protests|Election protests]] begin in Iran. * The [[Second Chechen War]] ends. * [[Boko Haram]] rebellion begins in Nigeria. * [[2009 swine flu pandemic]] began in [[North America]]. {{see also|2009#Deaths}}
==[[2010s]]==
===[[2010]]=== * [[January 12]]: A [[2010 Haiti earthquake|7.0 magnitude earthquake]] in [[Haiti]] kills 230,000. * [[February 18]]: [[2010 Nigerien coup d'état]]. * [[March 29]]: [[2010 Moscow Metro bombings]]. * [[April 10]]: The President of Poland, [[Lech Kaczyński]], is among 96 killed when their airplane [[2010 Polish Air Force Tu-154 crash|crashes]] in Smolensk. * [[April 20]]: The [[Deepwater Horizon oil spill|largest oil spill in US history]] occurs in the [[Gulf of Mexico]]. * [[May 10]]: [[Benigno Aquino III]] is elected as the [[List of Presidents of the Philippines|15th]] [[President of the Philippines]]. * [[May 11]]: After the [[2010 United Kingdom general election]], [[David Cameron]] becomes [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]]. * [[May 31]]: [[Gaza flotilla raid]]. * [[June 11]]–[[July 11]]: [[2010 FIFA World Cup|The FIFA World Cup]] is held in Africa for the first time. * [[July 22]]–[[August 10]]: [[2010 Colombia–Venezuela diplomatic crisis]]. * [[August 23]]: [[Manila hostage crisis]]. * [[November 23]]: [[North Korea]] [[Bombardment of Yeonpyeong|shells]] the island of [[Yeonpyeong]]. * [[2010 Thai military crackdown|A military crackdown]] occurs in [[Thailand]]. * The threat of [[Greece]] [[Greek government-debt crisis|defaulting on its debts]] triggers the [[2010 European sovereign debt crisis|European sovereign debt crisis]] and [[Republic of Ireland]]'s [[Post-2008 Irish economic downturn|financial crisis]]. * Burmese political prisoner [[Aung San Suu Kyi]] is released from house arrest. * [[Arab Spring]] starts. * [[Kyrgyz Revolution of 2010]]. * The [[Burj Khalifa]] in [[Dubai]] becomes the [[tallest structure in the world]], standing at 829.8&nbsp;m (2,722&nbsp;ft). * [[Dilma Rousseff]] is elected as the first female [[president of Brazil]]. * The [[iPad]] is introduced. * [[Instagram]] is launched. * [[2010 eruptions of Eyjafjallajökull]]. * [[Julia Gillard]] is elected first woman [[Prime Minister of Australia]]. {{see also|2010#Deaths}}
===[[2011]]=== * [[February 22]]: [[2011 Christchurch earthquake|Christchurch earthquake]] kills 185 and injures 2,000. * [[March 11]]: A [[2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami|9.0 earthquake]] in [[Japan]] triggers a tsunami and the [[Fukushima Daiichi nuclear disaster|meltdown of the Fukushima Nuclear Power Plant]]. * [[April 29]]: [[Wedding of Prince William and Catherine Middleton]]. * [[May 2]]: [[Death of Osama bin Laden|Osama bin Laden is shot dead]] by [[United States Navy SEALs]] in [[Pakistan]]. * [[July 9]]: Independence of [[South Sudan]]. * [[July 22]]: [[2011 Norway attacks]]. * [[August 6]]–[[August 11|11]]: [[2011 England riots|Riots flare across England]]. * [[October 20]]: [[Death of Muammar Gaddafi|Muammar Gaddafi is captured and killed]] during the [[Battle of Sirte (2011)|Battle of Sirte]]. * [[November 8]]: [[Activision]] release ''[[Call of Duty: Modern Warfare 3]]''. * [[World population]] [[The Day of Seven Billion|reaches 7 billion]]. * [[Snapchat]] launched. * [[Arab Spring]]: [[Tunisian revolution|revolutions in Tunisia]], [[2011 Egyptian revolution|Egypt]] [[2011 Libyan civil war|and Libya]] follow, as well as [[2011 Yemeni uprising|uprisings in Yemen]] [[2011 Bahraini uprising|and Bahrain]], and protests in several other Arab countries. * [[Syrian civil war]] begins. * [[Second Ivorian Civil War]]. * [[Occupy movement]] inspires worldwide protests. * [[News International phone hacking scandal]]. * [[Death and state funeral of Kim Jong-il]]. * The [[Danyang–Kunshan Grand Bridge]], the world's longest, opens in China. * [[Second Ivorian Civil War]] ends with the arrest of former president [[Laurent Gbagbo]]. * [[Withdrawal of U.S. troops from Iraq (2007–2011)|Iraq War ends]]. * Bombings occur [[Domodedovo International Airport bombing|in Russia]] [[2011 Mogadishu bombing|and Somalia]]. * [[2011 Sindh floods|Floods in Pakistan]], [[2011 Thailand floods|Thailand]] [[Tropical Storm Washi|and the Philippines]] kill roughly 2,500 people. * [[Space Shuttle program]] is officially ended. * [[NASA]] launches [[Juno (spacecraft)|space]][[Curiosity (rover)|craft]] to visit [[Jupiter]] and [[Mars]]. * [[Amazon rainforest|Amazon Rainforest]] and [[Amazon River|River]], [[Hạ Long Bay]], [[Jeju Island]], [[Iguazú Falls]], [[Puerto Princesa Subterranean River National Park|Puerto Princesa Underground River]], [[Komodo Island]] and [[Table Mountain]] were named as the world's [[New7Wonders of Nature]]. {{see also|2011#Deaths}}
===[[2012]]=== * [[January 13]]: [[Costa Concordia disaster]]. * [[February 6]]: The first episode of ''[[It's Showtime (Philippine TV program)|It's Showtime]]'' airs on [[ABS-CBN]]. * [[February 26]]: [[Killing of Trayvon Martin]]: The 17-year-old African-American high school student was killed in [[Sanford, Florida]]. * [[April 12]]: [[King (company)|King]] release ''[[Candy Crush Saga]]''. * [[May 7]]: [[Vladimir Putin]] is elected president of Russia for the third time. * [[July 15]]: [[Gangnam Style]], a [[K-pop]] song by South Korean rapper [[Psy]] is released and becomes the worldwide phenomenon due to recognition of ''[[Guinness World Records]]'' as the [[List of most-liked YouTube videos|most "liked" video on YouTube]] at the time. * [[July 20]]: [[2012 Aurora, Colorado shooting]]. * [[September 11]]–[[September 12|12]]: [[2012 Benghazi attack]] leads to the death of US ambassador [[J. Christopher Stevens]]. * [[October 9]]: Assassination attempt of schoolgirl [[Malala Yousafzai]]. * [[October 14]]: ** Skydiver [[Felix Baumgartner]] becomes the first person to [[Sound barrier#Breaking the sound barrier as a human projectile|break the sound barrier without a vehicle]]. ** [[FIGat7th]], reopens the newly constructed center which was happened in the fall of 2012.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://brighamyen.com/2012/10/05/city-target-opens-next-week-sprinkles-and-the-melt-sign-on-at-figat7th-in-downtown-la | title=City Target Opens Next Week, Sprinkles and the Melt Sign on at FIGat7th in Downtown LA &#124; DTLA RISING | date=5 October 2012 }}</ref> * [[October 22]]–[[November 22]]: [[Hurricane Sandy]] causes $70 billion in damage and kills 233 people. * [[November 6]]: Barack Obama wins second term as President of the United States, [[2012 United States presidential election|defeating former Massachusetts Governor Mitt Romney]]. * [[November 15]]: [[Xi Jinping]] is elected as [[General Secretary of the Chinese Communist Party]]. * [[November 26]]–[[December 8]]: [[2012 United Nations Climate Change Conference|UN Climate Change Conference]] agrees to extend the [[Kyoto Protocol]] until 2020. * [[December 4]]–[[December 9|9]]: [[Typhoon Bopha]] kills over 1,600 in the [[Philippines]]. * [[December 14]]: [[Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting]]. * The [[Higgs boson]] is discovered. * [[Central African Republic conflict (2012–13)|Conflict begins]] in the [[Central African Republic]]. * [[Israel]] launches [[Operation Pillar of Defense]] against the [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]]-governed [[Gaza Strip]]. * The US rover, [[Curiosity (rover)|Curiosity]], takes a selfie on [[Mars]] and finds evidence of an [[Water on Mars#Lakes and river valleys|ancient streambed of water]] on the Red Planet. * [[Diamond Jubilee of Elizabeth II]]. * The [[2012 Summer Olympics]] was hosted in [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]. * [[Park Geun-hye]] is elected [[President of South Korea]]. * [[Shenouda III]], [[Pope of the Coptic Orthodox Church of Alexandria]], departs; [[Pope Tawadros II of Alexandria|Tawadros II]] succeeds him. * [[Yemen]]i President [[Ali Abdullah Saleh]] steps down. * [[Mali War|Northern Mali conflict]], the [[National Movement for the Liberation of Azawad|MNLA]] declares [[Azawad]] an independent state. {{see also|2012#Deaths}}
===[[2013]]=== * [[February 15]]: An [[Chelyabinsk meteor|undiscovered meteor]] strikes the Chelyabinsk oblast in Russia, with an airburst injuring thousands and damaging many buildings. * [[February 28]]–[[March 13]]: [[Resignation of Pope Benedict XVI|Pope Benedict XVI resigns]], the first Pope to do since 1415, and [[Pope Francis]] is elected, becoming the first Pope from [[Latin America]]. * [[March 5]]: [[Death and state funeral of Hugo Chavez]]. * [[April 24]]: The [[2013 Savar building collapse|Rana Plaza collapses]] in [[Bangladesh]]. * [[May 22]]: [[British Army]] soldier [[Fusilier#United Kingdom|Fusilier]] [[Murder of Lee Rigby|Lee Rigby]] of the [[Royal Regiment of Fusiliers]] is murdered in [[Woolwich]], southeast [[London]] by Islamic terrorists Michael Adebolajo and Michael Adebowale. * [[July 3]]: [[President of Egypt]] [[Mohamed Morsi]] [[2013 Egyptian coup d'état|is deposed by the military in a coup d'état]]. * [[August 21]]: [[Ghouta chemical attack|A chemical attack in Ghouta, Syria]] is blamed on President [[Bashar al-Assad]]. * [[September 9]]–[[September 28|28]]: [[Zamboanga City crisis]]. * [[September 17]]: [[Rockstar Games]] release ''[[Grand Theft Auto V]]''. * [[October 15]]: A [[2013 Bohol earthquake|7.2 magnitude earthquake]] in [[Bohol]], kills 222. * [[November 8]]: [[Typhoon Haiyan]] kills nearly 6,150 people in [[Vietnam]] and the [[Philippines]]. * [[November 21]]: The [[Euromaidan]] protest begins in [[Ukraine]]. * [[December 5]]: [[Death and state funeral of Nelson Mandela]]. * The French military intervenes in the [[Northern Mali conflict]]. * [[Boston Marathon bombings|Terrorist attacks occur]] in [[Boston]] [[Westgate shopping mall attack|and Nairobi]]. * [[Edward Snowden]] releases classified documents concerning [[Global surveillance disclosure|mass surveillance by the NSA]]. * [[Croatia]] becomes a member of the [[European Union]]. * [[South Sudanese conflict (2013–present)|Conflict begins in South Sudan]]. * [[Uruguay]] becomes [[Legality of cannabis by country|the first country to fully legalize cannabis]]. * End of [[2012–2013 Cypriot financial crisis]]. * [[Kiss nightclub fire]]. * [[2013 Alberta floods]]. * [[2013 Lahad Datu standoff]]. * [[Guang Da Xing No. 28 incident]]. * [[Death and funeral of Margaret Thatcher]]. {{see also|2013#Deaths}}
===[[2014]]=== * [[February]]: [[Euromaidan]] protest in Ukraine sparks a [[Revolution of Dignity|revolution]] and the overthrow of [[Viktor Yanukovych]], leading to Russia's [[Annexation of Crimea by the Russian Federation|annexation of Crimea]] and the [[War in Donbas (2014–2022)|War in Donbas]]. * [[March 8]]: [[Malaysia Airlines Flight 370]] disappears from radar while en route to Beijing from Kuala Lumpur. There were 239 people on board. * [[April 16]]: The [[Sinking of MV Sewol|MV Sewol]] sinks, killing 304 of 476 passengers, 250 of which were students at [[Danwon High School]]. * [[May 22]]: A [[2014 Thai coup d'état|coup d'état]] in [[Thailand]] overthrows the caretaker government. * [[June 19]]: King [[Juan Carlos I]] of Spain abdicates; his son becomes [[King Felipe VI]]. * [[August 9]]: The [[shooting of Michael Brown|shooting]] of African-American teenager Michael Brown by police leads to [[Ferguson unrest|violent unrest]] in [[Ferguson, Missouri]]. * [[November 12]]: The [[Rosetta (spacecraft)|''Rosetta'' spacecraft]]'s ''[[Philae (spacecraft)|Philae]]'' probe becomes the first to successfully land on [[67P/Churyumov-Gerasimenko|a comet]]. * [[December 16]]: [[Tehrik-i-Taliban Pakistan]] [[2014 Peshawar school massacre|kill]] over 130 students in [[Pakistan]]. * [[Western African Ebola virus epidemic|The worst Ebola epidemic in recorded history]] occurs in West Africa, infecting nearly 30,000 people and resulting in the deaths of 11,000+. * The [[Yemeni Civil War (2014–present)|Yemeni Civil War]] begins after the [[Houthi takeover|Houthi takeover in Yemen]]. * [[Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501]] crashes into the Java Sea, while [[Malaysia Airlines Flight 17]] is shot down over Ukraine and [[Air Algérie Flight 5017]] is downed in [[Mali]]. * [[Israel]] launches [[Operation Protective Edge|an assault]] on the [[Gaza Strip]] in response to [[2014 kidnapping and murder of Israeli teenagers|tit-for-tat]] [[Kidnapping and murder of Mohammed Abu Khdeir|murder-kidnappings]], leading to the deaths of 71 Israelis and 2,100 Palestinians. * [[Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant|ISIS]] begins [[Northern Iraq offensive (June 2014)|its offensive in northern Iraq]], leading to [[2014 American-led intervention in Iraq|intervention in Iraq]] [[American-led intervention in Syria|and Syria]] by a US-led coalition. * [[Second Libyan Civil War]] begins. * [[Narendra Modi]] is elected as the Prime Minister of [[India]]. * [[Joko Widodo]] is [[2014 Indonesian presidential election|elected]] [[President of Indonesia]]. * [[Yeonmi Park]] delivers an emotional speech at the 2014 One Young World Summit. * [[Doha]], [[Durban]], [[Havana]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[La Paz]] and [[Vigan]] were chosen as the world's [[New7Wonders Cities]]. {{see also|2014#Deaths}}
===[[2015]]=== * [[January 1]]: Five [[former Soviet Union]] countries form the [[Eurasian Economic Union]]. * [[January 3]]–[[January 7|7]]: [[Boko Haram]] perpetrates [[2015 Baga massacre|a massacre of over 2,000 people]] in [[Baga, Nigeria]], and allies itself with [[Islamic State in Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]]. * [[April 2]]: [[Al-Shabaab (militant group)|Al-Shabaab]] perpetrates a [[Garissa University College attack|mass shooting]] in [[Kenya]], killing 148. * [[April 25]]–[[May 3]]: The [[Death of Freddie Gray|death]] of an African-American man, Freddie Gray by police leads to [[2015 Baltimore protests|violent unrest]] in [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]]. * [[May 3]]: [[Floyd Mayweather Jr. vs. Manny Pacquiao]]. * [[July 14]]: [[Iran nuclear deal|Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action]] agreement reached, setting limits to Iran's [[nuclear program of Iran|nuclear program]] in exchange for sanctions relief. * [[September 30]]: Russia begins [[Russian military intervention in Syria|air strikes]] against [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] and [[Syrian opposition|anti-government forces]] in Syria * [[November 30]]–[[December 12]]: [[2015 United Nations Climate Change Conference|195 nations agree]] to lower [[carbon emissions]]. * A [[November 2015 Paris attacks|series of terrorist attacks]] [[Charlie Hebdo shooting|occur in Paris]]. * [[April 2015 Nepal earthquake|A series]] [[May 2015 Nepal earthquake|of earthquakes]] [[October 2015 Hindu Kush earthquake|in the Himalayas]] kills over 10,000 people. * The heads of [[China]] and [[Taiwan]] [[2015 Ma–Xi meeting|meet for the first time]], while the [[United States]] and [[Cuba]] [[Cuban thaw|reestablish full diplomatic relations]]. * [[Water on Mars|Liquid water]] is found on [[Mars]]. * First [[Dawn (spacecraft)|close]][[New Horizons|-up]] images of [[Ceres (dwarf planet)|Ceres]] and [[Pluto]]. * [[China]] announces the end of [[One-child policy]] after 35 years. * [[European migrant crisis]]. * The [[Supreme Court of the United States]] determines that [[same-sex marriage in the United States|same-sex couples have a constitutional right to marry]]. * The opposition-led [[Democratic Unity Roundtable]] wins the most seats in the [[2015 Venezuelan parliamentary election]], defeating the [[United Socialist Party of Venezuela]] for the first time since the [[National Assembly (Venezuela)|National Assembly]] was established in 1999. * [[Homo naledi]], a species of early human, is discovered in Africa. * Crash of [[Germanwings Flight 9525]]. * [[Volkswagen emissions scandal]]. * [[Charleston church shooting]]. * [[Assassination of Boris Nemtsov]]. * [[2015 FIFA corruption case]]. {{see also|2015#Deaths}}
===[[2016]]=== * [[January 8]]: [[El Chapo]] is recaptured following his escape from a high-security prison in Mexico. * [[February 11]]: Detection of [[gravitational wave]]s by [[LIGO]] confirmed. * [[March 20]]: [[Barack Obama]] becomes the first U.S. president to visit [[Cuba]] since [[Calvin Coolidge]] in 1928. * [[April 3]]: [[Panama Papers]], a [[news leak|leak]] of legal documents, reveals information of 214,888 [[offshore companies]]. * [[April 13]]: The [[Golden State Warriors]] set the NBA single-season victory mark by notching their 73rd win in the season's final game. The Warriors finished the regular-season with a 73–9 record. * [[May 9]]: [[Rodrigo Duterte]] becomes [[President of the Philippines]], and initiates [[Philippine Drug War|a controversial drug war]]. * [[June 1]]: The [[Gotthard Base Tunnel]], the world's longest and deepest [[railway tunnel]], is completed. * [[June 12]]: A shooter [[Orlando nightclub shooting|kills 49 people]] at a gay nightclub in [[Orlando, Florida]]. * [[June 23]]–[[July 13]]: The people of the [[United Kingdom]] vote to [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum|leave the European Union]]; [[David Cameron]] [[Resignation of David Cameron|resigns]] as a result, and [[Theresa May]] succeeds him as the second female [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom|Prime Minister]] of the UK. * [[July 4]]: [[Juno (spacecraft)|Juno]] enters orbit into [[Jupiter]]. * [[September 4]]: [[Mother Teresa]] is officially [[canonized]] by [[Pope Francis]]. * [[October 25]]–[[November 2]]: [[Chicago Cubs]] wins the [[2016 World Series|World Series]] for the first time since [[1908 World Series|1908]], ending the [[Curse of the Billy Goat]]. * [[November 4]]: The [[Paris Agreement]], signed by 195 nations to fight [[global warming]], formally goes into effect. * [[November 8]]: [[Donald Trump]] wins the [[2016 presidential election]], in an upset against [[Hillary Clinton]], the first female to be nominated for a major party. * The [[United Nations]] lifts sanctions from [[Iran]] in recognition of the dismantling of its [[Iran and weapons of mass destruction|nuclear program]]. * [[Pope Francis]] and [[Patriarch Kirill]] sign the [[Joint Declaration of Pope Francis and Patriarch Kirill|Ecumenical Declaration]]. * [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|ISIL]] claims responsibility for [[2016 Brussels bombings|a series of bombings in Brussels]], [[2016 Atatürk Airport attack|a massacre]] at [[Istanbul]]'s [[Atatürk Airport]] and car ramming attacks in [[2016 Nice truck attack|Nice]]. * [[Augmented-reality]] game, [[Pokémon Go]], is released, breaking records in revenue, and becoming the best-selling mobile game. * The [[Colombia]]n government signs a [[Colombian peace process|peace deal]] with [[FARC]] to end the [[Colombian conflict]], despite narrowly losing [[2016 Colombian peace agreement referendum|a referendum]]. * The government of [[Turkey]] begins a [[2016 Turkish purges|series of purges]] in reaction to a [[2016 Turkish coup d'état attempt|failed coup d'état attempt]]. * The [[2016 Summer Olympics]] take place in [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]]. * [[Withdrawal of U.S. troops from Afghanistan|United States troops withdraw from Afghanistan]] after 15 years. * The [[President of Brazil]], [[Dilma Rousseff]], is impeached. * [[Vajiralongkorn]] becomes [[King of Thailand]]. * [[Andrei Karlov]], the Russian Ambassador to Turkey, [[Assassination of Andrei Karlov|is assassinated]] at an art exhibition in Ankara. * [[Tsai Ing-wen]] is [[2016 Taiwanese presidential election|elected]] as the first female [[President of the Republic of China|President of Taiwan]]. * [[2016 attack on the Saudi diplomatic missions in Iran]]. * [[2016 Russian Defence Ministry Tupolev Tu-154 crash]]. * [[Trial of Radovan Karadžić|Radovan Karadžić found guilty of 10 of 11 counts of war crimes, genocide and crimes against humanity and is sentenced to 40 years in prison]]. * [[July 2016 Dhaka attack|Dhaka attack]] kills 29 people. * [[Panama Canal expansion project|A third set of locks in the Panama Canal opens for commercial traffic]]. * [[2016 Southern Taiwan earthquake]]. * [[2015–2016 Zika virus epidemic|An outbreak of the Zika virus]] is linked to a cluster of cases of [[microcephaly]]. * [[Death and state funeral of Fidel Castro]]. * [[TikTok]] is launched. {{see also|2016#Deaths}}
===[[2017]]=== * [[January 20]]: [[Donald Trump]] is inaugurated as President of the United States. * [[January 21]]: Millions of people participated in the [[2017 Women's March|Women's March]], as a response to the inauguration of Donald Trump. * [[February 13]]: [[Kim Jong-nam]], the half-brother of [[Kim Jong-Un]], [[Assassination of Kim Jong-nam|is assassinated in Kuala Lumpur]]. * [[May 13]]: [[Pope Francis]] canonizes [[Jacinta and Francisco Marto]], two of the three [[Our Lady of Fátima#Later years of the children|Fátima children]] who reported seeing the Virgin Mary in the spring and summer of 1917. * [[May 22]]: A [[Manchester Arena bombing|terrorist bombing attack]] at an [[Ariana Grande]] concert in [[Manchester, England]] kills 22 people and injures over 140. * [[May 23]]: [[Proclamation No. 216|Martial law]] declared in Mindanao following [[Marawi crisis|clashes between Philippine government forces and the Maute group in Marawi]]. * [[June 2]]: [[2017 Resorts World Manila attack|36 people are killed in an attack in Resorts World Manila]]. * [[July 4]]: Russia and China urge North Korea to halt its missile and nuclear programs after it successfully tested its first intercontinental ballistic missile.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-40497972|title=North Korea missile test: Russia and China urge freeze in launches |date=July 4, 2017|work=BBC News|access-date=July 4, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/07/03/asia/north-korea-missile-japan-waters/index.html|title=North Korea tests missile it claims can reach 'anywhere in the world' |date=July 4, 2017|publisher=CNN|access-date=July 4, 2017}}</ref> * [[August 11]]–[[August 12|12]]: The city of [[Charlottesville, Virginia|Charlottesville]] is [[Unite the Right rally|the site of a far-right rally]] protesting the removal of [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] statues throughout the US. During the event, a white supremacist rams his car into a crowd of counter-protesters, injuring 19 and [[Heather Heyer|killing one]]. * [[August 21]]: A [[Solar eclipse of August 21, 2017|solar eclipse]] passes throughout the [[contiguous United States]] for the first time since [[Solar eclipse of June 8, 1918|1918]]. * [[September]]: Two earthquakes strike Mexico on [[2017 Chiapas earthquake|September 8]] and [[2017 Central Mexico earthquake|September 19]], killing over 400 people. * [[October 1]]: [[2017 Las Vegas shooting|60 people are killed in a mass shooting at a music festival in Las Vegas]]. * [[October 14]]: A [[14 October 2017 Mogadishu bombings|bombing in Mogadishu, Somalia]] on October 14, kills 587 people and injures 316. It is one of the deadliest terrorist attacks in modern history. * [[October 16]]: [[Abu Sayyaf]] leader [[Isnilon Hapilon]] and [[Maute group]] leader [[Omar Maute]] are killed by government troops in an operation of rescuing the hostages. * [[October 17]]: Pres. [[Rodrigo Duterte]] declares the liberation of [[Marawi City]], with more than a thousand reportedly killed in the [[Battle of Marawi|battle]]. * [[October 28]]: [['Oumuamua]], the first known [[interstellar object]], is identified. * [[November 5]]: [[Sutherland Springs church shooting|26 people are killed in a church in Sutherland Springs, Texas]]. * Tensions between [[North Korea]] and the [[UN]] escalate as the country [[2017 North Korean nuclear test|tests a hydrogen bomb]] and conducts [[2017 North Korean missile tests|a series of ballistic missile tests]]. The UN responds with a wave of export sanctions. * [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] (ISIL) launch [[2017 Tehran attacks|simultaneous attacks]] in [[Tehran]], destroy the [[Great Mosque of al-Nuri (Mosul)|Great Mosque of al-Nuri]] in [[Mosul]] [[Iraq]], and [[2017 Sinai mosque attack|kill 311 in Egypt]], but are declared defeated in Iraq by the end of the year. * [[2017–18 North Korea crisis]] begins as [[North Korea]] conducts a series of missile and nuclear tests that demonstrate its ability to launch ballistic missiles beyond its immediate region. * A [[Rohingya persecution in Myanmar (2016–present)|military operation]] targeting [[Rohingya people|Rohingya Muslims]] in [[Myanmar]] is declared [[ethnic cleansing]] by the [[UNHCR]]. * [[2017 Atlantic hurricane season|This year's Atlantic Hurricane season]] features [[Hurricane Harvey]], which kills 107 and becomes the costliest hurricane in US history, as well as [[Hurricane Irma]], killing 134, and [[Hurricane Maria]], killing 3,059. * [[Robert Mugabe]] is ousted in a [[2017 Zimbabwean coup d'état|coup d'état]], while [[Ratko Mladić]] is declared guilty of genocide. * [[Harvey Weinstein sexual abuse cases|Allegations of sexual abuse]] against [[film producer]] [[Harvey Weinstein]] lead to a [[Weinstein effect|wave of similar accusations]] from within [[Hollywood, Los Angeles|Hollywood]] and other areas of primarily the English-speaking world. * [[Nintendo]] launches the [[Nintendo Switch]]. * [[Grenfell Tower fire]] in London kills 72 and injures 70. * The [[President of South Korea]], [[Park Geun-hye]], is impeached, while [[Moon Jae-in]] [[2017 South Korean presidential election|is elected]] [[President of South Korea|president]]. * [[Emmanuel Macron]] becomes President of France after defeating [[far-right]] candidate [[Marine Le Pen]]. * A [[2017 Venezuelan constitutional crisis|constitutional crisis]] occurs in Venezuela after [[2017 Venezuelan Constituent Assembly election|Constituent Assembly elections]] which replaced the legislative powers held by the opposition-led [[National Assembly (Venezuela)|National Assembly]]. {{see also|2017#Deaths}}
===[[2018]]=== * [[March 24]]: [[March for Our Lives]] occurs in 900 locations worldwide in response to the 14 February [[Stoneman Douglas High School shooting|Parkland shooting]]. * [[June 12]]: The first summit between [[2018 North Korea–United States summit|the US and North Korea]] and the first ever crossing of the [[Korean Demilitarized Zone]] by a North Korean leader occur. * [[June 23]]-[[July 10]]: Twelve boys and their football coach are successfully [[Tham Luang cave rescue|rescued]] from the flooded [[Tham Luang Nang Non]] cave in [[Thailand]]. * [[June 24]]: Saudi Arabia [[Women to drive movement|allows women to drive]]. * [[October 2]]: Exiled ''[[Washington Post]]'' journalist [[Jamal Khashoggi]] is [[Assassination of Jamal Khashoggi|assassinated]] inside the Saudi consulate in Istanbul, triggering a [[Reactions to the assassination of Jamal Khashoggi|diplomatic crisis]] for Saudi Arabia. * [[November 25]]: [[Kerch Strait incident]] triggers martial law in [[Ukraine]]. * [[Turkey]] [[Operation Olive Branch|invades northern Syria]], while 70 die in [[Douma chemical attack|a chemical attack]], triggering a [[2018 missile strikes against Syria|missile strike]] against [[Bashar al-Assad]]. * [[Pakatan Harapan]] becomes the first opposition party to assume power in [[Malaysia]] since independence. * Twenty-year [[Eritrean–Ethiopian border conflict]] formally ends. * [[Yellow vests movement]] becomes [[France]]'s largest sustained period of civil unrest since 1968. * The [[2018 Sunda Strait tsunami|Sunda strait tsunami]] kills 426 and injures 14,000 and the [[2018 Sulawesi earthquake and tsunami]] kills 4,340 and injures 10,700. * [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] and [[Greece]] reach a historic agreement in the [[Macedonia naming dispute]], in which the former is renamed in 2019 to the 'Republic of North Macedonia'. * China's [[National People's Congress]] votes to abolish presidential [[term limits]], allowing [[Xi Jinping]] to [[President for life|rule for life]]. Xi is also the [[General Secretary of the Chinese Communist Party]], the [[Paramount leader|highest position]] without term limits. * [[China–United States trade war]] begins. * [[2018 Armenian revolution]] occurs. * [[2018 Iraqi parliamentary election|First post-ISIS election in Iraq]]. * [[Death and state funeral of George H. W. Bush]] * [[France]] wins the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia. * [[First World War centenary|Leaders from more than 40 international organizations and dignitaries from nearly 200 countries attends the centennial of the ending of the First World War]]. * [[Bill Cosby sexual assault cases|Bill Cosby found guilty of drugging and sexually assaulting a woman and is sentenced to three to ten years in prison]]. * The Trump administration reimposes [[sanctions against Iran]]. * The first monkeys are [[Cloning|cloned]], and first genetically modified humans reported, in China. * [[Jacob Zuma]] resigns as [[President of South Africa]]; [[Cyril Ramaphosa]] becomes President. * [[Scott Morrison]] becomes [[Prime Minister of Australia]]. * Four people are poisoned, one to death, in [[Poisoning of Sergei and Yulia Skripal|Salisbury]] and [[2018 Amesbury poisonings|Amesbury]], England in a suspected Russian assassination attempt. The British government responds by leading the international expulsion of 153 Russian diplomats. * The [[northern white rhinoceros]] becomes [[functionally extinct]]. * The university professor [[Giuseppe Conte]] becomes [[Prime Minister of Italy]] at the head of a populist coalition. * [[Ángela Ponce]] becomes the first openly [[transgender]] woman to represent Spain in the [[Miss Universe 2018]]. {{see also|2018#Deaths}}
===[[2019]]=== * [[January 3]]: [[Chang'e 4]] becomes the first object to land on the [[far side of the Moon]]. * [[April 10]]: ** The [[Event Horizon Telescope]] takes the first ever image of a [[black hole]], at the core of galaxy [[Messier 87]]. ** Fossil fragments found in the [[Callao Cave]] in the [[Philippines]] reveal the existence of the ''[[Homo luzonensis]]'' species of humans. * [[April 15]]: A major [[Notre-Dame de Paris fire|fire]] engulfs [[Notre-Dame de Paris|Notre-Dame Cathedral]] in Paris, resulting in the roof and main spire collapsing. * [[April 30]]: [[Emperor of Japan|Emperor]] [[Akihito]] of [[Japan]] [[2019 Japanese imperial transition|abdicates]] from his [[Chrysanthemum Throne|throne]], the first abdication by a Japanese monarch in almost two centuries. The abdication ends the [[Heisei]] [[Japanese era names|era of Japan]] and ushers in the [[Reiwa|Reiwa era]] with new emperor [[Naruhito]] ascending the throne on May 1. * [[August 5]]: [[India]] [[Revocation of the special status of Jammu and Kashmir|revokes the special status of Jammu and Kashmir]]. * [[September 19]]: An [[2019–2020 Philippines polio outbreak|outbreak of polio]] is declared in the Philippines, 19 years following its eradication in the country. * [[October 18]]: [[NASA]] astronauts [[Jessica Meir]] and [[Christina Koch]] conduct the first all-female spacewalk outside of the [[International Space Station|ISS]]. * [[December 18]]: [[President of the United States|U.S. President]] [[Donald Trump]] is [[First impeachment of Donald Trump|impeached]] by the [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] for abuse of power and obstruction of Congress. * [[December 24]]: 50 people are killed and thousands are left homeless by [[Typhoon Phanfone]] in the [[Philippines]]. * ''[[New Horizons]]'' takes the first close up image of a [[486958 Arrokoth|classical kuiper belt object]]. * [[Christchurch mosque shootings]] kill 51 people, while a [[2019 Khash–Zahedan suicide bombing|suicide bombing in Iran]] kills 41, and a [[2019 Sri Lanka Easter bombings|series of bomb attacks]] in [[Sri Lanka]] kills 250. * The [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant]] loses the last of its territory. * [[Abdelaziz Bouteflika]] resigns as [[President of Algeria]], while [[Omar al-Bashir]] [[2019 Sudanese coup d'état|is deposed]] as [[President of Sudan]] in [[2019 Sudanese coup d'état|a coup d'état]] amid [[2019 Algerian protests|widespread protests]] [[2018–19 Sudanese protests|in both countries]]. * [[Victor Vescovo]] breaks the human depth record, reaching 10,928&nbsp;m in the [[Challenger Deep]]. * [[2019–20 Hong Kong protests|Protests begin]] in [[Hong Kong]] over an extradition bill. * [[2019 Amazon rainforest wildfires|Wildfires spike]] in [[Brazil]], while [[Australia]] endures the [[2019–20 Australian bushfire season|most widespread brush fires in its history]]. * ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' was released in theaters, breaking many box-office records, including becoming the [[List of highest-grossing films|highest-grossing movies of all time]]. * Isabelle Holdaway is the first patient to receive a genetically modified [[phage therapy]] to treat a [[Antimicrobial resistance|drug-resistant infection]]. * [[Pope Francis]] abolishes [[Pontifical secret|pontifical secrecy]] in [[Catholic Church sexual abuse cases|sex abuse cases]]. * The [[2019–2020 dengue fever epidemic]] begins in [[Southeast Asia]]. * [[Jair Bolsonaro]] becomes [[President of Brazil]]. * [[2019—20 Bolivian protests|Protests erupt in Bolivia]] [[2019 Venezuelan presidential crisis|and Venezuela]] over [[2018 Venezuelan presidential election|disputed]] [[2019 Bolivian general election|elections]]. * [[Nursultan Nazarbayev]] resigns as [[President of Kazakhstan]]. [[Kassym-Jomart Tokayev]] assumes power. [[Astana]] is renamed [[Nur-Sultan]] in his honor. * The EU [[Directive on Copyright in the Digital Single Market]] is passed over intense opposition. * [[Volodymyr Zelenskyy]] becomes [[President of Ukraine]]. * [[Bashar al Assad]] launches [[Northwestern Syria offensive (April–August 2019)|multiple offensives]] [[Northwestern Syria offensive (November 2019–present)|in Northwestern Syria]]; [[Turkey]] launches [[2019 Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria|an offensive into northeastern Syria]]. * [[Khartoum massacre|More than a hundred people are killed]] after police and [[Janjaweed]] attack protesters in Sudan. * The United States blames [[June 2019 Gulf of Oman incident|attacks on ships in the Gulf of Oman]] on Iran, escalating tensions in the Persian Gulf. * [[Kyriakos Mitsotakis]] becomes [[Prime Minister of Greece]]. * [[Boris Johnson]] becomes [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]], and attempts a [[2019 British prorogation controversy|prorogation of Parliament]] that is [[R (Miller) v The Prime Minister and Cherry v Advocate General for Scotland|ultimately declared unlawful]]. * [[Barisha raid]] ends in the [[Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi|death of Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi]]. * [[2019 Albania earthquake|A 6.4 magnitude earthquake]] in [[Albania]], kills 51 people. * [[Greta Thunberg]] delivers "How dare you" speech at the [[2019 UN Climate Action Summit]]. * The [[United States Department of Justice|U.S. Justice Department]] charges Chinese tech firm [[Huawei]] with multiple counts of fraud. * [[WikiLeaks]] co-founder [[Julian Assange]] is [[Indictment and arrest of Julian Assange|arrested]] in London. * More than 50 prisoners are [[Amazonas prison massacres|killed in a series of riots]] in [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], Brazil. * [[2019 Koreas–United States DMZ Summit|A trilateral gathering was held at the Panmunjom Truce Village between South Korean President Moon Jae-in, North Korean Leader Kim Jong-un and United States President Donald Trump]]. * [[Ursula von der Leyen]] becomes [[President of the European Commission]]. * [[United States v. Guzmán|Joaquín "El Chapo" Guzmán found guilty of drug trafficking, money laundering and murder and is sentenced to 30 years in prison]]. * [[2019–2020 Japan–South Korea trade dispute|Japan and South Korea trade dispute]]. * [[Death of Sahar Khodayari|Sahar Khodayari]] dies after setting herself on fire after being arrested for attending a soccer game in [[Iran]]. * [[Trial of Catalonia independence leaders|Twelve Catalan independence movement leaders found guilty of sedition and misuse of public funds and they were sentenced to 9 to 13 years in prison]]. * Israeli Prime Minister [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] is indicted on charges of bribery, fraud and breach of trust. * [[Sanna Marin]] becomes [[Prime Minister of Finland]]. {{see also|2019#Deaths}}
